The PEARL Awards Nigeria has announced that the 25th edition will take place later in the year. To this end, the Central Working Committee (CWC) of the 2022 PEARL Awards was inaugurated last week Thursday. This according to the President, PEARL Awards, Mr. Tayo Orekoya, kick-starts activities that will culminate in the hosting of the awards on the last Sunday of November each year. Orekoya said, the 2022 PEARL Awards with the theme: ‘Sustaining Excellence Through Tenacity (SETT)’, reflects current realities of the PEARL Awards, our corporates and capital markets, locally and globally.   UBEC to carry out fresh headcount of primary, secondary…     Community leader Agbator for burial Friday     Pernod Ricard shines at Kantar awards   It would be recalled that the awards were not held in 2020 and 2021 due to the devastating impact of COVID-19 pandemic on businesses and events around the globe, including Nigeria. Orekoya stated that “PEARL is faced with the herculean task of bringing back the awards fully to the corporate space of Nigeria after two years of inactivity.” “The yearnings of our stakeholders for the Pearl Awards to return cannot be over-emphasized and therefore we must do everything possible to ensure that this year’s Awards surpasses their expectations.” Mrs. Ifeoma Adibe-Chukwuka has been appointed chairman of its CWC.  She heads a 15- man committee of top-flight professionals charged with proffering ideas, initiatives and innovations that would make the 2022 edition fundamentally different.